cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.Distributed Systems, cs.HC, cs.OH

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper describes a distributed application for monitoring and fault injection in a parallel computing system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the quality of fault-tolerance design in a software application. 
- cs.Distributed Systems is another possible category as the application is distributed and involves communication between different components. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of a World-Wide Web browser as a hypermedia monitor, which involves interaction between the user and the system. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a catch-all category that could apply if the paper does not fit neatly into any of the other categories.
